     <span class="pb center" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-08-02-pb-0378">[378<a style="padding-left: 0px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-08/ADMS-06-08-02-pb-0378.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a>]</span>
     <div class="docback">
      <div class="note-source" id="PJA08d266sn1">
       <p>
        <span class="docSource"><span class="dType"><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ recipients copy (A recipients copy is assumed to be in the hand of the signer unless it is otherwise described.) ]">RC</abbr></span> (<span class="ref-terms">Adams Papers</span>); addressed: Mr. J. Adams Hotel de Valois rue de Richelieu; docketed: M. Genet. 28. Feb. 1780. ansd. 29.</span>
       </p>
      </div>
      <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA08d266n1-ptr" id="PJA08d266n1">1</a>
       <p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> did so in his letter of <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-08-02-0255" class="document">29 Feb.</a> to the president of the congress (calendared, below). There he stated that Genet had already translated and published the Constitutions of New York, New Jersey, Pensylvania, Maryland, Virginia and South Carolina.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA08d266n2-ptr" id="PJA08d266n2">2</a>
       <p>This sentence is in Genets hand.</p>
